BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..subtitle: Crucible Handler
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..name: Lord Shaxx
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..description: The Crucible is the arena in which Guardians forge their Light. Lord Shaxx is the Crucible.

interactions.flavorLineOne: Shaxx, looking even more animated than usual, welcomes you to a new world of Valor and Gloryand encourages you to test your prowess in the newly ranked Crucible.
"We have all borne witness to your journey, Guardian. But I know you still have some things undone. Use this to finish what they started." Lord Shaxx, to Josef
It seems unlikely that Shaxx will remove his helmet to consume the cookies, but that doesn't mean he isn't grateful.
Lord Shaxx gives you a nod of a approval. You can't see it, but he's smiling under his helm.

"Tremendous! I always knew you had an eye for the battlefield, and you've proven it this day," Shaxx bellows.

"Take this weapon. Think of it not as a gift, but as a promise, an oath to uphold the same level of discipline and vigilance you showed here any time you set foot in a combat zone. We'll all be safer under your watch."

Shaxx chuckles. "Well, all but your Crucible opponents. I'm looking forward to your next match, Guardian."
Lord Shaxx has a gift for you: a Ghost Shell that will track your victories.

"The Festival of the Lost is a special time for us, Guardian," Lord Shaxx says, inclining his head. "Although we do not fear death, we must respect it. But during this holiday, we can laugh at death. We can shed a little light on the unknowable thing and celebrate that we are always one step ahead."

He puts his hands on his hips. "No better way to laugh at death than dying, again and again, in the Crucible! HA HA HA HA!!"
"She used to glow with pride when you'd return from a match." Lord Shaxx, to Josef
Lord Shaxx's voice already sounds better even though the package of lozenges remains unopened. Still, he seems grateful.
Shaxx congratulates you and your Crimson Bond on battles hard-fought and victories hard-won during Crimson Daysand offers a handsome reward with his inspiring words.
As you are a Fabled competitor in the Crucible, Shaxx wishes to reward your efforts.
You have become a Legend in the Crucible. Shaxx wishes to bask in your glory.
Your efforts in the Crucible have become Legend. Time to begin your story anew.

"Ahh, another brave Guardian ready to test their might. The Crucible awaits!"

Lord Shaxx offers bounties, quests, and special rewards for competing in the Crucible.

The Crucible is a player-vs-player activity. Face other Guardians, alone or with your fireteam, to gain XP and unique rewards including weapons and gear.

Lord Shaxx is impressed when you return. "The Crucible is fast-paced, even chaotic at times," he says. "That you can pull off such a careful, precise shot under those conditions Anyone on the other side of your scope should be worried. Well done!"
"Your old life is over, Redrix. This is different from your birth as an Exo and your rebirth as a Guardian. Now, you are an icon. Let that guide your future." Lord Shaxx
Shaxx looks at you differently now. He offers you the weapon he used those many years ago at Twilight Gap, and wishes you well when you carry it into battle.
"I had a feeling I'd be handing this over to you," Shaxx booms. He collects your new Recluse and hands it over with a respectful nod. "Do the children proud."
As boisterous as ever, Shaxx speaks warmly (and loudly) of Crimson Daysand of his challenge to Guardians who choose to celebrate with him in the Crucible.

"All blades dull with time, Guardian," Shaxx says with a stern nod.

"The work you've done here will keep yours sharp, for now. Good effort, but I expect you back soon."

"You're already making a name for yourself in the Crucible, Guardian. But don't let up. Keep fighting!"

Solo, or with a fireteam, the Crucible helps Guardians master their combat skills against the toughest competition: other Guardians.

Complete Crucible matches and Crucible bounties to gain XP and earn rewards, including weapons, gear, and more!

"Are you ready to step up to the challenge, Guardian?"

Crucible bounties offer focused objectives for Guardians to complete while competing in Crucible playlists.

Select Crucible bounties from Lord Shaxx. Complete their objectives, then turn in the completed bounties to gain XP and rewards.
Your reputation in the Crucible precedes you. Take this reward in recognition of your deeds.
Complete bounties for XP and undertake quests for valuable gear. Completing Crucible matches grants you tokens, which can be turned in here for packages.
Show Lord Shaxx proof of your deeds in the Crucible.
Increase your level to claim these rewards.
Your reputation in the Crucible precedes you. Take this reward in recognition of your deeds.

failureStrings: Requires completion of the "A Display of Power" pursuit.
Requires completion of the "Fighting in Style" quest.
